1️⃣ Docker Introduction
👉 What is Docker?

Docker is a tool that helps you:

Package + Run applications in isolated environments called containers

🧠 Simple Example:

Instead of saying:

“Install Java”
“Install MySQL”
“Set environment variables”

👉 You just say:

“Run my Docker container”

And everything works 💯

🚨 Why Docker?

Because:

"It works on my machine" problem ❌
Different OS issues ❌
Dependency conflicts ❌
2️⃣ Problem We Are Trying To Solve
❌ Problems before Docker:
Different environments:
Dev → Test → Prod (all different)
Dependency issues:
Java 8 vs Java 17
Different libraries
Installation pain:
Setup takes hours
🧠 Real Example:

You build Spring Boot app → works locally
But on server → crashes 😵

3️⃣ Solution with Virtualization (VM)
👉 What is VM?

A Virtual Machine is:

A full computer inside your computer

Structure:
Hardware
  ↓
Hypervisor
  ↓
VM (OS + App)
✅ Advantages:
Isolation ✔️
Multiple OS ✔️
❌ Problems:
Heavy (GBs of size)
Slow startup
Each VM has full OS
4️⃣ Solution with Containerization
👉 What is Container?

Lightweight environment that shares OS kernel

Structure:
Hardware
  ↓
Host OS
  ↓
Docker
  ↓
Containers (App + Dependencies)
✅ Advantages:
Lightweight ⚡
Fast 🚀
Portable 💯
🔥 Key Difference:
Feature	VM	Container
Size	Large	Small
OS	Full OS	Shared OS
Speed	Slow	Fast
5️⃣ What is Docker (Deep)
👉 Docker = Platform for Containerization
🧩 Main Components:
Docker Engine
Core runtime
Docker Image
Blueprint (like class)
Docker Container
Running instance (like object)
Docker Hub
Online storage for images
🧠 Flow:
Dockerfile → Image → Container
